# Project structure

Monorepo with clearly separated back and front. Keep new files in the right place.

```text
backend/     # Spring Boot modular monolith (Java 21, Maven)
             #   src/main/java/com/ngs/analytics/{auth,upload,domain,analytics,fastq,vcf,projects,reports,common}
frontend/    # Angular 19 app
             #   src/app/pages   -> page components
             #   src/app/core    -> shared services, guards, interceptors
spark-jobs/  # Spark local jobs (Phase 2)
docker/      # Compose + Dockerfiles + nginx/prometheus config
datasets/    # tiny public fixtures only
data/        # local runtime uploads + H2 (gitignored)
docs/        # architecture and API notes
```

- Keep backend and frontend strictly separated; no shared build.
- Stay a **modular monolith** — do not split into microservices.
- New backend feature: add to the matching `com.ngs.analytics` package, not a new module.
- New Angular page: `frontend/src/app/pages`; shared logic: `frontend/src/app/core`.
